{{Infobox figure skater |name= Kendra Moyle |image= Kendra Moyle & Andy Seitz - 2006 Skate Canada.jpg |caption=Moyle and Seitz in 2006. |country= [[United States]] |birth_date= {{birth date and age|1990|9|17}} |residence= |height= {{convert|161|cm|ft|abbr=on}} |partner= '''[[Steven Pottenger]]''' |formerpartner= [[Andy Seitz]] |coach= [[Adrienne Lenda]], [[Johnny Johns]] |choreographer=[[Igor Shpilband]], [[Marina Zoueva]], [[Olga Volozhinskaia]] |skating club= Arctic FSC |retired= |combined total= 136.78 |combined date= [[2006 Cup of Russia]] |SP score= 51.21 |SP date= [[ISU Junior Grand Prix|2006 JGP Liberec]] |FS score= 89.58 |FS date= [[2006 Skate Canada]] }} '''Kendra Moyle''' is an [[United States|American]] [[pair skater]]. She previously skated with [[Andy Seitz]]. Together, they are the 2006 US Junior national champions and won the silver medal at the 2006 World Junior championships. They are skated on both the Junior Grand Prix and senior Grand Prix circuit in the 2006/2007 season. Moyle and Seitz announced the end of their partnership on April 4, 2007. Moyle has teamed up with [[Steven Pottenger]].
Before teaming up with Seitz, Moyle skated with [[Reed Minney]].
